"title": "4954: morning",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4954: morning",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The period of time roughly between dawn and noon. Morning was an assigned time for worship, sacrifice and prayer. The morning light uncovers events of the night and provides opportunity for renewed daily activity. God's blessings are received new every morning, and the start of a new day symbolises renewal and hope.</p>\n<h2>Morning as the start of a new day</h2>\n<h3>The period of time created by God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:5\">GEN 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:8\">GEN 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:13-Exod18:14\">EXO 18:13–18:14</a> <em>The working day is reckoned from morning till evening</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:21\">EXO 27:21</a> <em>The night is reckoned from evening till morning</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job38:12\">JOB 38:12</a></p>\n<h3>The transience of morning mist</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:22\">ISA 44:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:4\">HOS 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:3\">HOS 13:3</a></p>\n<h3>Morning as a symbol of renewed hope</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps30:5\">PSA 30:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:6\">PSA 130:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa21:11-Isa21:12\">ISA 21:11–21:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:19\">ISA 26:19</a></p>\n<h3>The Messiah brings a new morning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal4:2\">MAL 4:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:19\">2PE 1:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:78-Luke1:79\">LUK 1:78–1:79</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:12\">ROM 13:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:8\">1JN 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:28\">REV 2:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:16\">REV 22:16</a></p>\n<h3>The sky in the morning</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:3\">MAT 16:3</a></p>\n<h2>Morning as an opportunity for activity</h2>\n<h3>A time for travel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:2\">GEN 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:3\">GEN 22:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:55\">GEN 31:55</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:21\">NUM 9:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num22:21\">NUM 22:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:1\">JOS 3:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:20\">1SA 17:20</a></p>\n<h3>A time for battle</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh8:10-Josh8:14\">JOS 8:10–8:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:33\">JDG 9:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs3:21-2Kgs3:23\">2KI 3:21–3:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:20\">2CH 20:20</a></p>\n<h3>A time to begin daily labour</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:7\">RUT 2:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl11:6\">ECC 11:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:1\">MAT 20:1</a></p>\n<h3>A time to begin important activity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:13\">EXO 9:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:2-Exod34:4\">EXO 34:2–34:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:15\">EXO 7:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod8:20\">EXO 8:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:26\">1KI 18:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:12\">ACT 23:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:23\">ACT 28:23</a></p>\n<h3>A time to respond to nightly revelation</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen20:8\">GEN 20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:18\">GEN 28:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:8\">GEN 41:8</a></p>\n<h3>A time to administer justice</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer21:12\">JER 21:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph3:5\">ZEP 3:5</a></p>\n<h2>Morning as a time of revelation</h2>\n<h3>A time of discovery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:25\">GEN 29:25</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs19:35\">2KI 19:35</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa37:36\">ISA 37:36</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:27-Gen19:28\">GEN 19:27–19:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:28\">JDG 6:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam5:4\">1SA 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:14\">ISA 17:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:21\">1KI 3:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs6:15\">2KI 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:18\">ACT 12:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:5\">1CO 4:5</a></p>\n<h3>Morning brings God's revelation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:7-Exod16:8\">EXO 16:7–16:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:5\">NUM 16:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh7:14\">JOS 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:19\">1SA 9:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa50:4\">ISA 50:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek12:8\">EZK 12:8</a></p>\n<h2>Morning devotions</h2>\n<h3>A time for offering sacrifices</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:13-Ezek46:15\">EZK 46:13–46:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:38-Exod29:40\">EXO 29:38–29:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod36:3\">EXO 36:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:3-Num28:5\">NUM 28:3–28:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:40\">1CH 16:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:4\">2CH 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr13:11\">2CH 13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:20-2Chr29:21\">2CH 29:20–29:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:5\">JOB 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>A time for prayer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:13\">PSA 88:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:3\">PSA 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:17\">PSA 55:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:35\">MRK 1:35</a></p>\n<h3>A time to praise God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:1-Ps92:3\">PSA 92:1–92:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:30\">1CH 23:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps59:16\">PSA 59:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps65:8\">PSA 65:8</a></p>\n<h3>Priestly duties each morning</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:7\">EXO 30:7</a> <em>burning incense</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:12\">LEV 6:12</a> <em>making the burnt offering</em></p>\n<h2>God's blessings are received new each morning</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:22-Lam3:23\">LAM 3:22–3:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:12-Exod16:15\">EXO 16:12–16:15</a> <em>God's provision of manna in the desert</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs17:6\">1KI 17:6</a> <em>God supplies Elijah with food</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:14\">PSA 90:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:2\">ISA 33:2</a></p>",
